   <abstract>Both Odunayo and Wereszczak, who work at UT College of Veterinary Medicine, mentioned one particular cat named Topper. He was the most severely burned of nearly 20 “firecats” that were treated in Emergency Critical Care at UTCVM. Topper had severe face and foot pad burns, but “he was a trooper.” He and his owner had a happy reunion three days later. Topper’s story spread and resulted in a Facebook page for people to follow his recovery progress.</abstract>
